.TH "file_open_name" 9 "file_open_name" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
file_open_name \- open file and return file pointer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct file *" file_open_name
.BI "(struct filename *name "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ","
.BI "umode_t mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
struct filename containing path to open
.IP "flags" 12
open flags as per the open(2) second argument
.IP "mode" 12
mode for the new file if O_CREAT is set, else ignored
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is the helper to open a file from kernelspace if you really
have to.  But in generally you should not do this, so please move
along, nothing to see here..
